-- Chilean Minister Forecasts Rate Hold Next Week, Financiero Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-03-08T14:56:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/chilean-minister-forecasts-rate-hold-next-week-financiero-says.html
Chile’s Economy Minister Pablo Longueira said it’s “probable” the central bank will keep its
key  interest rate  unchanged next week after consumer prices grew
a faster-than-forecast 0.4 percent in February,  Diario
Financiero  reported.  The minister was speaking at a ceremony in Santiago, the
Santiago-based newspaper  reported  on its website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 